<br>
I want the epic.   I'm willing to pay even 100K, 200K for the thing.   I could make that kind of money in two, maybe 3 months.   I don't see why I have to go camp for all the quest components, and then get a couple raids going for the boss mobs.  I'd hate to lose out on a roll for the Earth staff, and argue with some other Mage over it, considering how difficult it is for me to attend a Planes raid.  It is just not going to happen for me as a 2-hour a night kind of player.<br>
<br>
We are talking about options for people that just cannot do the Jboots quest in this thread, and most people think it is really good.   What about us that will never get our epic?   Heck, Jboots are coveted, that is why you get the whining, KSing, etc.  But, yeah, they are not &quot;Uber.&quot;   So, a nerfed Jboots might be sold that cost 5-6K.   OK, thats great for twinks, I really feel good for em.   So 100&lt;-&gt;200K for the Epic is about fair, I think, if we are comparing value.   Its going to take a lot of time investment, farming, HG smashing to get that kind of money.  This is not a trivial sum, and is even out of the &quot;twinking&quot; range pretty much.   The nice thing is that I can do it as a casual player -- I don't have to put in 20+ hours to get to Isle 6 or 7 in PoA, or attend every raid to kill Inney and pray for a loot of the Staff.  Or kill endless greenies looking for my Torn Pages of Magi'kot.   Or power of Fire gems.   I can do my time in the Rathe Mountains.  Or farm Kunark.  Or buy/sell in GFay.<br>
<br>
I can do this on my own limited schedule.  A couple hours a night.<br>
<br>
I don't think it would affect people that already have Epics...hey they were the first ones to get them, I'm happy for them, but I'd like a way to get mine too.   100-200K is a lot of cash.  Think of the money sink this would be.<br>
<br>
Its all good. <p><b>Seek Pyremaker</b><br>
Mage 49th Season, Spec-Evocation, Xegony<br>
Proud member of "The Ring of Truth"
